cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on unsupervised depth prediction using monocular images. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper discusses the challenges of training the network for pose estimation in indoor environments, which is relevant to robotics. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category as the paper proposes novel loss functions and an ensemble learning approach to improve the accuracy of depth prediction. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper uses deep learning techniques to solve the depth prediction problem. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible category as the paper deals with continuous video streams and proposes a flipping strategy and median filter to improve the output disparity map.
